Standard Bank Passes Absa as Biggest Mortgage Lender, FM Says

-- B y   S i k o n a t h i   M a n t s h a n t s h a
-- 
2011-06-01T10:56:48Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-01/standard-bank-passes-absa-as-biggest-mortgage-lender-fm-says.html
Standard Bank  Group Ltd. overtook
 Absa Group Ltd. (ASA)  to become  South Africa ’s largest residential
mortgage lender in December, the Johannesburg-based  Financial
Mail  reported.  Standard Bank’s share has climbed to 28 percent, wrote the
magazine without saying where it obtained the information.  The latest banks supervision report of the  South African
Reserve Bank  shows Standard Bank had residential mortgage assets
of 247.1 billion rand ($36.4 billion) in December, while Absa
had 243.5 billion rand, according to the central bank’s website.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sikonathi Mantshantsha in Johannesburg at 
 smantshantsh@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at 
 gserkin@bloomberg.net  